content.problem_latex:
$$\overline{**45}$$, $$\overline{19*8}$$, $$\overline{23*1}$$, and $$\overline{3*49}$$ are four $4-$digit numbers with some unknown digits. Which number is possible to be a perfect square?
(A) \overline{**45}
(B) \overline{19*8}
(C) \overline{23*1}
(D) \overline{3*49}
(E) None
